headline: Why Molina Healthcare (MOH) Stock Is Falling Today
summary: Shares of healthcare insurance company Molina Healthcare (NYSE:MOH) fell 4.8% in the morning session after Barclays lowered its price target on the stock. The investment bank adjusted its price target to $185 from a previous $186. While the reduction is minor, price target changes from financial institutions are closely watched by investors.
